    `_updated_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage column for _updated_at | Column _updated_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `auto_renew_disabled_date` DATE COMMENT 'The date when the subscriber disabled auto-renewal for their subscription. Null if auto-renewal was never disabled. Used to identify planned churn versus reactive churn. | Column auto_renew_disabled_date (DATE) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `cancellation_channel` STRING COMMENT 'The interface or channel through which the cancellation was initiated. Supports analysis of churn patterns by customer touchpoint. [ENUM-REF-CANDIDATE: web_self_service|mobile_app|customer_care|email|chat|ivr|mvpd_drop|system_automated â€” 8 candidates stripped; promote to reference product] | Column cancellation_channel (STRING) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `cancellation_reason_code` STRING COMMENT 'Standardized code representing the stated reason for cancellation. Used for churn analytics and product improvement initiatives. Empty value_regex indicates reference to external reason code lookup table with more than 6 values. | Column cancellation_reason_code (STRING) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `cancellation_reason_description` STRING COMMENT 'Free-text description or additional details provided by the subscriber explaining the reason for cancellation. Supports qualitative churn analysis. | Column cancellation_reason_description (STRING) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `ccpa_opt_out_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Boolean indicator of whether the subscriber exercised CCPA opt-out rights regarding data sale or sharing. Used for privacy compliance and marketing eligibility. | Column ccpa_opt_out_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `churn_prediction_score` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The machine learning model-generated churn risk score that was assigned to the subscriber prior to the churn event. Range 0.0000 to 1.0000, where higher values indicate higher churn risk. Used for model validation and predictive accuracy assessment. | Column churn_prediction_score (DECIMAL(5,4)) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `churn_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The exact date and time when the subscriber cancellation or lapse event occurred. This is the business event timestamp representing when the subscriber relationship ended. | Column churn_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `churn_type` STRING COMMENT 'Classification of the churn event based on the nature of cancellation. Voluntary indicates subscriber-initiated cancellation, involuntary indicates business-initiated termination, payment failure indicates cancellation due to billing issues. | Column churn_type (STRING) in subscriber.churn_event. Valid values are `voluntary|involuntary|payment_failure|trial_expiration|promotional_end|service_termination`',
    `competitor_service_mentioned_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Boolean indicator of whether the subscriber mentioned switching to a competitor service during the cancellation process. Used for competitive intelligence and market positioning analysis. | Column competitor_service_mentioned_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `created_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column created_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `created_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The timestamp when this churn event record was first created in the system. Used for audit trail and data lineage tracking. | Column created_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `currency_code` STRING COMMENT 'Three-letter ISO 4217 currency code for the last payment amount. Supports multi-currency subscription operations. | Column currency_code (STRING) in subscriber.churn_event. Valid values are `^[A-Z]{3}$`',
    `customer_care_contact_count` STRING COMMENT 'The number of customer care interactions the subscriber had in the 30 days prior to churn. Used to identify service quality issues and early warning signals. | Column customer_care_contact_count (INT) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `days_since_last_viewing` STRING COMMENT 'The number of days between the last viewing activity and the churn event. Used for engagement-based churn prediction models. | Column days_since_last_viewing (INT) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `device_count_at_churn` STRING COMMENT 'The number of registered devices associated with the subscriber at the time of churn. Used for multi-device engagement analysis. | Column device_count_at_churn (INT) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `final_access_date` DATE COMMENT 'The last date the subscriber had active access to content and services. May differ from churn_timestamp due to grace periods or paid-through dates. | Column final_access_date (DATE) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `gdpr_data_deletion_requested_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Boolean indicator of whether the subscriber requested deletion of their personal data under GDPR right to erasure at the time of churn. Used for privacy compliance tracking. | Column gdpr_data_deletion_requested_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `last_payment_amount` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The monetary value of the last successful payment received from the subscriber before churn. Used for ARPU (Average Revenue Per User) and revenue impact analysis. | Column last_payment_amount (DECIMAL(15,2)) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `last_payment_date` DATE COMMENT 'The date of the last successful payment received from the subscriber before churn. Used for revenue recognition and payment failure analysis. | Column last_payment_date (DATE) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `last_viewing_date` DATE COMMENT 'The date of the subscribers last content viewing activity before churn. Used to identify engagement drop-off patterns and at-risk subscriber signals. | Column last_viewing_date (DATE) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `notes` STRING COMMENT 'Free-text field for additional notes, comments, or context about the churn event captured by customer care agents or system processes. | Column notes (STRING) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `parental_control_enabled_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Boolean indicator of whether parental controls were enabled on the subscription at the time of churn. Used for family-oriented subscriber segmentation and churn analysis. | Column parental_control_enabled_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `payment_failure_count` STRING COMMENT 'The number of consecutive payment failures that occurred before the churn event. Used to identify involuntary churn patterns and dunning effectiveness. | Column payment_failure_count (INT) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `promotional_discount_active_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Boolean indicator of whether the subscriber had an active promotional discount at the time of churn. Used to analyze price sensitivity and promotional effectiveness. | Column promotional_discount_active_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `reactivation_eligibility_date` DATE COMMENT 'The date when the churned subscriber becomes eligible for reactivation campaigns or promotional offers. Used for win-back campaign targeting and timing. | Column reactivation_eligibility_date (DATE) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `service_tier` STRING COMMENT 'The subscription service tier that was cancelled. SVOD (Subscription Video On Demand), AVOD (Advertising-Supported Video On Demand), TVOD (Transactional Video On Demand). | Column service_tier (STRING) in subscriber.churn_event. Valid values are `svod|avod|tvod|premium|basic|bundle`',
    `source_record_id` STRING COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column source_id (STRING) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `subscription_tenure_months` STRING COMMENT 'The total number of months the subscriber maintained an active subscription before churning. Used for cohort analysis and LTV (Lifetime Value) calculations. | Column subscription_tenure_months (INT) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `total_lifetime_revenue` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The cumulative revenue generated from this subscriber across their entire subscription tenure. Used for LTV (Lifetime Value) analysis and churn impact assessment. | Column total_lifetime_revenue (DECIMAL(15,2)) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `updated_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column updated_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `updated_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The timestamp when this churn event record was last modified. Used for audit trail and change tracking. | Column updated_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `win_back_offer_accepted_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Boolean indicator of whether the subscriber accepted the win-back offer. True indicates acceptance and retention, False indicates rejection and churn completion. Null if no offer was presented. | Column win_back_offer_accepted_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.churn_event',
    `win_back_offer_presented_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Boolean indicator of whether a retention or win-back offer was presented to the subscriber during the cancellation process. True indicates an offer was made, False indicates no offer was presented. | Column win_back_offer_presented_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.churn_event',
    CONSTRAINT pk_churn_event PRIMARY KEY(`churn_event_id`)
) COMMENT 'Operational record of a subscriber cancellation or lapse event. Captures cancellation timestamp, cancellation channel (self-service, customer care, payment failure, MVPD drop), stated cancellation reason, win-back offer presented flag, win-back offer accepted flag, and reactivation eligibility date. Supports churn rate reporting and retention campaign targeting. Distinct from analytics â€” this is the operational event record. | Unity Catalog table: media_broadcasting_ecm.subscriber.churn_event';

