    `revenue_stream_id` BIGINT COMMENT 'Foreign key linking to finance.revenue_stream. Business justification: Promotional offers affect revenue stream classification and promotional revenue tracking for financial reporting. Finance separates promotional revenue from standard pricing for margin analysis and re | Column revenue_stream_id (BIGINT) in finance.offer_redemption',
    `employee_id` BIGINT COMMENT 'Foreign key linking to workforce.employee. Business justification: Sales and retention agents process promotional offer redemptions via phone/chat channels. Required for agent commission calculations, sales performance tracking, and offer redemption audit trails in s | Column sales_agent_employee_id (BIGINT) in workforce.offer_redemption',
    `subscriber_id` BIGINT COMMENT 'Reference to the subscriber who redeemed the promotional offer. Links to the subscriber master record. | Column subscriber_id (BIGINT) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `subscription_id` BIGINT COMMENT 'Reference to the specific subscription instance that was created or modified as a result of this offer redemption. Links to the subscription record. | Column subscription_id (BIGINT) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `_created_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage column for _created_at | Column _created_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `_source_code` BIGINT COMMENT 'Medallion lineage column for _source_id | Column _source_id (STRING) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `_updated_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage column for _updated_at | Column _updated_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `applied_discount_amount` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The monetary value of the discount applied to the subscription as a result of this redemption. Expressed in the subscription currency. | Column applied_discount_amount (DECIMAL(15,2)) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `attribution_source` STRING COMMENT 'The marketing source or touchpoint that led to this offer redemption. Examples include email campaign, social media ad, affiliate link, or organic search. Used for marketing attribution analysis. | Column attribution_source (STRING) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `created_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column created_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `created_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The date and time when this offer redemption record was first created in the system. Used for audit trail and data lineage tracking. | Column created_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `discount_duration_months` STRING COMMENT 'The number of months for which the discount will be applied to the subscription. Null for one-time discounts or permanent pricing changes. | Column discount_duration_months (INT) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `discount_percentage` DECIMAL(18,2) COMMENT 'The percentage discount applied when discount_type is percentage. Null for non-percentage discount types. Expressed as a decimal (e.g., 25.00 for 25% off). | Column discount_percentage (DECIMAL(5,2)) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `discount_type` STRING COMMENT 'The type of discount mechanism applied through this offer redemption. Determines how the discount value is calculated and applied to the subscription. | Column discount_type (STRING) in subscriber.offer_redemption. Valid values are `percentage|fixed_amount|free_trial|upgrade_credit|bundle_discount`',
    `eligibility_failure_reason` STRING COMMENT 'Detailed explanation of why the redemption was rejected or marked ineligible. Null if redemption was successful. Used for customer service and offer optimization. | Column eligibility_failure_reason (STRING) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `eligibility_verified_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Indicates whether the subscribers eligibility for the offer was verified at the time of redemption. True if eligibility checks passed, False otherwise. | Column eligibility_verified_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `first_time_subscriber_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Indicates whether this redemption resulted in a new subscriber acquisition (True) or was redeemed by an existing subscriber (False). Critical for Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC) and Lifetime Value (LTV) analysis. | Column first_time_subscriber_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
    `offer_expiration_date` DATE COMMENT 'The date on which the promotional offer expires and can no longer be redeemed. Used to validate redemption eligibility and track expired redemption attempts. | Column offer_expiration_date (DATE) in subscriber.offer_redemption',
