    `employee_id` BIGINT COMMENT 'Foreign key linking to workforce.employee. Business justification: GDPR/CCPA consent changes requiring manual review are processed by compliance staff. Essential for regulatory audit trails, consent dispute resolution, and compliance team workload tracking in privacy | Column processed_by_employee_id (BIGINT) in workforce.subscriber_consent_record',
    `subscriber_id` BIGINT COMMENT 'Unique identifier of the subscriber to whom this consent record applies. Links to the subscriber master entity. | Column subscriber_id (BIGINT) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `_created_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage column for _created_at | Column _created_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `_source_code` BIGINT COMMENT 'Medallion lineage column for _source_id | Column _source_id (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `_updated_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage column for _updated_at | Column _updated_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `collection_channel` STRING COMMENT 'The channel or interface through which the consent was collected. Identifies the touchpoint where the subscriber provided or withdrew consent. [ENUM-REF-CANDIDATE: web|mobile_app|call_center|email|in_person|api|third_party â€” 7 candidates stripped; promote to reference product] | Column collection_channel (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `communication_channel_preference` STRING COMMENT 'The subscribers preferred communication channel for receiving messages related to this consent type. Governs operational routing of communications. | Column communication_channel_preference (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record. Valid values are `email|push_notification|sms|in_app_message|postal_mail|phone_call`',
    `consent_audit_trail_reference` STRING COMMENT 'External reference or identifier linking this consent record to detailed audit logs or supporting documentation. Supports regulatory audit and compliance verification. | Column consent_audit_trail_reference (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `consent_expiry_date` DATE COMMENT 'The date on which this consent expires and must be re-confirmed. Nullable for consents without expiration. Supports time-bound consent management. | Column consent_expiry_date (DATE) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `consent_scope_description` STRING COMMENT 'Detailed description of the scope and purpose of the data processing covered by this consent. Provides business context for the consent type. | Column consent_scope_description (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `consent_source_ip_address` STRING COMMENT 'The IP address from which the consent action was initiated. Used for fraud detection and audit trail verification. | Column consent_source_ip_address (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `consent_status` STRING COMMENT 'Current status of the consent. Indicates whether the subscriber has granted, withdrawn, or not provided consent for the specified activity. | Column consent_status (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record. Valid values are `granted|withdrawn|pending|expired|not_provided`',
    `consent_text_presented` STRING COMMENT 'The exact text of the consent disclosure or opt-in language presented to the subscriber at the time of consent. Immutable record for legal compliance and audit. | Column consent_text_presented (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `consent_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The exact date and time when the consent action was captured. Represents the business event time of the consent grant or withdrawal. | Column consent_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `consent_type` STRING COMMENT 'The specific type of data processing or communication activity for which consent is being recorded. Defines the scope of the consent grant or withdrawal. | Column consent_type (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record. Valid values are `marketing_email|personalization|data_sharing|third_party_analytics|childrens_data_processing|targeted_advertising`',
    `consent_version` STRING COMMENT 'Version identifier of the consent policy or terms presented to the subscriber at the time of consent. Enables tracking of consent under different policy versions. | Column consent_version (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `created_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column created_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `created_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The date and time when this consent record was first inserted into the system. Immutable audit field for record creation tracking. | Column created_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `data_retention_period_days` STRING COMMENT 'The number of days for which subscriber data may be retained under this consent. Nullable if no specific retention period applies. Governs data lifecycle management. | Column data_retention_period_days (INT) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `double_opt_in_confirmation_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The date and time when the subscriber confirmed their consent via double opt-in. Nullable if double opt-in is not required or not yet confirmed. | Column double_opt_in_confirmation_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `double_opt_in_confirmed_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Indicates whether the subscriber has confirmed their consent through a double opt-in process (e.g., email confirmation link). True if double opt-in is complete. | Column double_opt_in_confirmed_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `jurisdiction` STRING COMMENT 'Three-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 country code representing the legal jurisdiction under which this consent was collected. Determines applicable privacy regulations. | Column jurisdiction (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record. Valid values are `^[A-Z]{3}$`',
    `last_modified_timestamp` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'The date and time when this consent record was last updated. For immutable audit trail design, this should remain equal to created_timestamp unless metadata corrections are applied. | Column last_modified_timestamp (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `opt_in_method` STRING COMMENT 'The method by which the subscriber provided consent. Distinguishes between explicit opt-in, implicit acceptance, and other consent mechanisms. | Column opt_in_method (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record. Valid values are `explicit_checkbox|implicit_acceptance|verbal_confirmation|written_signature|electronic_signature|pre_checked_box`',
    `parental_consent_required_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Indicates whether parental or guardian consent is required for this subscriber under COPPA or equivalent regulations. True if the subscriber is a minor requiring parental consent. | Column parental_consent_required_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `parental_consent_verified_flag` BOOLEAN COMMENT 'Indicates whether parental consent has been verified through an acceptable verification method. True if verification is complete and valid. | Column parental_consent_verified_flag (BOOLEAN) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `preferred_language` STRING COMMENT 'Three-letter ISO 639-2 language code representing the subscribers preferred language for consent communications and disclosures. | Column preferred_language (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record. Valid values are `^[A-Z]{3}$`',
    `source_record_id` STRING COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column source_id (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `third_party_processor_name` STRING COMMENT 'Name of the third-party data processor or partner to whom data may be shared under this consent. Nullable if consent does not involve third-party sharing. | Column third_party_processor_name (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `updated_at` TIMESTAMP COMMENT 'Medallion lineage tracking column for bronze->silver->gold tracing | Column updated_at (TIMESTAMP) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    `withdrawal_reason` STRING COMMENT 'Free-text or coded reason provided by the subscriber for withdrawing consent. Nullable for granted consents. Supports churn analysis and compliance reporting. | Column withdrawal_reason (STRING) in subscriber.subscriber_consent_record',
    CONSTRAINT pk_subscriber_consent_record PRIMARY KEY(`subscriber_consent_record_id`)
) COMMENT 'Authoritative record of subscriber data privacy consents, opt-in/opt-out preferences, and communication channel preferences required under GDPR, CCPA, and COPPA. Captures consent type (marketing email, personalization, data sharing, third-party analytics, childrens data processing), communication channel preferences (email, push, SMS, in-app, postal), preferred language, consent status, consent timestamp, consent version, collection channel, and jurisdiction. Immutable audit trail â€” new records are inserted for each consent or preference change rather than updating existing rows. Governs both legal compliance and operational communication routing. | Unity Catalog table: media_broadcasting_ecm.subscriber.subscriber_consent_record';

